1 Type Syntax
 Dart uses the var keyword to achieve the same. 
 Example
   var name = 'Smith';
  void main() { 
    String name = 1; 
  }
  2.The dynamic keyword
   Variables declared without a static type are implicitly declared as dynamic.
   Example
   void main() { 
    dynamic x = "tom"; 
    print(x);  
    }
 3.Final and Const
  The final and const keyword are used to declare constants. 
 3.1 Syntax: final Keyword
   final variable_name
    OR
   final data_type  variable_name
   Example
   void main() { 
   final val1 = 12; 
   print(val1); 
 }
3.2 Syntax: const Keyword
const variable_name
OR
const data_type variable_name
 Example:
   void main() { 
   const pi = 3.14; 
   const area = pi*12*12; 
   print("The output is ${area}"); 
  }
  

